handovers will be facilitated by [name];

communication between the parties must be confined to issues concerning the child[ren] [and must only be by text message/email. The telephone numbers/email addresses of the parties are [insert]];

a ‘contact handover book’ shall be used to note any matters of concern of importance which one party needs to tell the other. The book is to be used solely for communication about spending time arrangements and the health and welfare of the child[ren][and must not be used to criticise or verbally abuse the other parent]. The book must be passed from one party to the other at handovers and must be brought to court on each occasion the parties attend;

[name] must not drink alcohol or use non-prescribed drugs for 24 hours before, or at any time while, seeing the child[ren];

contact will only take place if [name] provides a negative breathalyser sample at the start of any session when requested to do so. The testing kit is to be provided by [name].

the contact is to be supervised at all times by [name].

Child[ren] giving evidence

There shall be a hearing on [date] to consider whether the child[ren] should give oral evidence. In preparation for that hearing:

[Insert] must by [date] make available any ABE interview of the child[ren] to be viewed by the judge and all parties;

(where there is a pending criminal investigation or prosecution) [Insert] must give notice to the [police] / [CPS] that a decision will be made at the hearing whether the child[ren] should give evidence in these proceedings and that they may either send written representations or attend the hearing to express any views they have;

[Cafcass] / [CAFCASS Cymru] / [The child[ren]’s guardian [name]] must by [date] send to the court and to the parties a report in respect only of the child[ren] subject of these proceedings to whom the question of giving evidence relates dealing with the following issues in relation to the question whether the child[ren] should give oral evidence:

the child[ren]’s wishes and feelings, in particular the child[ren]’s willingness to give evidence;

the child[ren]’s particular needs and abilities;

the maturity, vulnerability and understanding, capacity and competence of the child[ren];
